Sentencas: Internal reforming of ethanol fuel was investigated on high-performance metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) with infiltrated catalysts.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications

Sentencas: The hydrogen concentration and internal reforming effects were evaluated systematically with different fuels including: hydrogen, simulated reformate, anhydrous ethanol, ethanol water blend, and hydrogen-nitrogen mixtures.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications

Sentencas: A simple infiltration of Ni reforming catalyst into 40 vol% Ni-Sm0.20Ce0.80O2.delta (Ni-SDCN40) and fuel-side metal support leads to complete internal reforming, as confirmed by comparison to simulated reformate.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications

Sentencas: The performance difference between hydrogen and fully-reformed ethanol is attributed entirely to decrease in hydrogen concentration.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications

Sentencas: High peak power density was achieved for a range of conditions, for example 1.0 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C in ethanol-water blend, and L4 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C in anhydrous ethanol fuel.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications

Sentencas: Initial durability tests with ethanol-water blend show promising stability for 100 h at 700 degrees C and 0.7 V. Carbon is not deposited in the Ni-SDCN40 anode during operation.
Titulo: Ethanol internal reforming in solid oxide fuel cells: A path toward high performance metal-supported cells for vehicular applications
